name: Somethin' Else
comments: THE LEGEND OF CANNONBALL, BLOW BABY BLOW!!! A TRUE JAZZ MASTER R I P
One of my early inspirations on alto, along with Johnny Hodges. Typically wonderful blowing on this tune, love the call and response parts, and bass all the way through is simply steaming.
think i'm finally getting into cannonball...this is sweet...
blue note classic...adderley (alto sax)...miles davis(t)...art blakey(d)...hank jones (p)...sam jones (b)
Oh, I forgot, nice tune. I love Cannonball....he's kind of underrated and overlooked.
shaielb, Wow, you must really like this song, hahahahaha!
This is so good: it makes me want to eat processed cheese.
One of the best jazz albums of all time. Just blows my mind.
